{"title_page": "2008 World Wrestling Championships", "text_new": "{{Infobox FILA wrestling event\n|Name = 2008 World Championships\n|Logo = 2008 FILA Wrestling World Championships logo.png\n|Size = 180\n|Host city ={{flagicon|JPN}} [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]\n|Optional caption =\n|Events = \n|dates = 11\u201313 October\n|Stadium = [[Yoyogi National Gymnasium]]\n|Women = {{JPN}}\n|Previous = [[2007 World Wrestling Championships|2007]]\n|Next = [[2009 World Wrestling Championships|2009]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2008 [[World Wrestling Championships]]''' were held at the [[Yoyogi National Gymnasium]] in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]. The event took place from October 11 to October 13, 2008.  The competition only featured wrestling in the [[Female]] [[Freestyle wrestling|Freestyle]] event.  Traditionally, Wrestling World Championships are not held in [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] years, but in 2008 a female championship was held because the [[Wrestling at the Summer Olympics|2008 Summer Olympics]] included only four of the seven [[International Federation of Associated Wrestling Styles|FILA]] weight classes for females.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themat.com/specialevents/2008/wwttrials/default.php |title=TheMat.com - The Ultimate Source of Real Wrestling! |publisher=Themat.com |accessdate=2008-11-06 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081121022802/http://www.themat.com/specialevents/2008/wwttrials/default.php |archivedate=November 21, 2008 |url-status=dead }} </ref>\n\n==Medal table==\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = \n | flag_template  = flagcountry\n | event          = \n | team           = \n | gold_JPN = 4 | silver_JPN = 1 | bronze_JPN = 2\n | gold_CAN = 1 | silver_CAN = 0 | bronze_CAN = 2\n | gold_USA = 1 | silver_USA = 0 | bronze_USA = 1\n | gold_BUL = 1 | silver_BUL = 0 | bronze_BUL = 0\n | gold_RUS = 0 | silver_RUS = 2 | bronze_RUS = 0\n | gold_CHN = 0 | silver_CHN = 1 | bronze_CHN = 2\n | gold_UKR = 0 | silver_UKR = 1 | bronze_UKR = 2\n | gold_BLR = 0 | si